經濟系大學部課程摘要







經濟學系  Department of Economics


中英文課程簡介

2011/11/14更新

經濟學原理  


經一  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本科目講授經濟行為、決策之基本原理及經濟問題之分析方法。教學內容分為個體經濟學與總體經濟學兩大部份。前者包括消費者行為、生產者行為、市場結構、生產要素市場、所得分配、市場失靈與政府乾預、公共選擇。後者包括國民所得衡量、所得決定理論、通貨膨脹與失業、總合需求行為、貨幣政策、財政政策。此外，如何將經濟學中重要觀念應用在日常生活中亦是本課程重要訓練之一。

 

PRINCIPLES OF ECONOMICS

Freshman  required  (3-3)

This course discusses 
microeconomics and macroeconomics.  In microeconomics we discuss consumer’s and 
firm’s behaviors, market structure, input market, income distribution, market 
failure and government intervention, and public choice.  In macroeconomics 
topics such as measurement of GDP, inflation and unemployment, aggregate demand 
and supply, monetary policy, and fiscal policy are discussed. The application of 
economic concepts in daily life is also emphasized in this course.

 

經濟學原理  


經一B  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本科目講授經濟學基本原理，上學期講授個體經濟學，包含 1.需求、供給與市場均衡分析，2.消費者行為均衡，.生產、成本與不同市場結構下的廠商利潤極大行為，以及4.市場失靈與公共選擇。下學期講授總體經濟學，包含：1.國內所得、通貨膨脹與失業之定義與衡量，2.短期總體模型，3.貨幣供給與利率理論，4.長期總體模型，以及5.貨幣與財政政策有效性比較。

 

PRINCIPLES OF ECONOMICS

Freshman  required  (3-3)

This course covers basic 
principles of economics. The first semester discusses microeconomic issues, 
including: 1. demand, supply and market equilibrium analysis; 2. the utility 
maximizing behavior of consumer, 3. production, costs and the firms’ profit 
maximization behavior in different industry structures and 4. market failure and 
public choice. The second semester discusses macroeconomics, including: 1. the 
definition and measurement of GDP, inflation and unemployment, 2. short-run 
macroeconomic model, 3. money supply and interest rate theory, 4. long-run 
macroeconomic model, and 5. the effectiveness of monetary and fiscal policies.

 

經濟學原理  


經一C  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本科目講授經濟行為、決策之基本原理及經濟問題之分析方法。教學內容分為個體經濟學與總體經濟學兩大部份。前者包括消費者行為、生產者行為、市場結構、生產要素市場、所得分配、市場失靈與政府乾預、公共選擇。後者包括國民所得衡量、所得決定理論、通貨膨脹與失業、總合需求行為、貨幣政策、財政政策、供給面經濟學。

 

PRINCIPLES OF ECONOMICS

Freshman  required  (3-3)

This course covers economic 
behaviors, principles of decision-making, and methods of economic analysis. 
Subjects are divided into two parts: microeconomics and macroeconomics. The 
former includes consumer choice theory, producer’s behaviors, market structures, 
factor markets, income distribution, market failure and government intervention, 
and public choice theory. The latter includes national income, theories of 
income determination, inflation and unemployment, aggregate demand, monetary 
policy, fiscal policy, and the supply side economics. 

 

 

會計學

經一  　必修 
　 ( 3 - 3 )


本課程教學內容涵括基本會計觀念的介紹、會計循環處理程序、複式分錄記錄之運用、財務報表的編製、財報分析及相關的決策制定等。並配合實習課程，以加強初學者之會計操作處理能力。

本課程講授章節共有十個主題，內容包括：(1)
會計的基本觀念介紹、(2) 會計循環之完成、(3)
買賣業會計、(4) 內部控制及現金之處理、(5)
應收款項會計處理、(6)長期性資產會計處理、(7)
負債會計處理、(8) 公司會計、(9)財務報表編製、(10)
財報分析。

 


Accounting


Freshman  required  (3-3)


This course includes the introduction of basic accounting concept, accounting 
cycle procedure, record of double entry and the utilization, prepare of 
financial statement.  It also provides the users of financial analysis and 
decision making and best practice by means of on-line train.


This course includes 10 tops are (1) Why Accounting Matters, (2) Understanding 
and complete the accounting cycle process, (3) Accounting for Merchandisers, (4) 
Internal Control Systems and Cash, (5) Receivables Accounting, (6) Long-term 
Assets Accounting, (7) Accounting for Liabilities, (8) Corporate Accounting, (9) 
Prepared Financial Statements, (10) Analyzing Financial Statements.

 

微積分       


經一  必修  
(3-3)
   
本科目介紹數學裡最常應用於商業、經濟上的幾個概念和方法。內容包括：(1)極限與微分(2)微分的應用：變動率、極值、最佳化問題、估算、隱函數微分(3)指數與對數函數(4)積分：定積分、重積分、積分的應用(5)多變數函數及偏微分：多變數函數的極值、限制條件下的極值、Lagrange方法(6)三角函數(7)泰勒多項式與無窮級數。
CALCULUS
Freshman required (3-3)

   This course introduces several important mathematics concepts and approaches 
used      in business and economics. It covers：(1) 
Limits and the deriative.(2) Applications of the derivative：rate 
of change, relative extrema, optimization problems, estimation, implicit 
differentiation.(3) The exponential and natural logarithmic functions.(4) 
Integration：definite 
integral, double integral, applications of the integral.(5) Functions of several 
variables and partial derivatives：maxima 
and minima of functions of several variables, constrained optimization, 
Lagrange's method.(6) The trigonometric functions.(7) Taylor polynomials and 
infinite series.

 

電子計算機概論 


經一  選修  
(2-0)


教導學生從認識電腦軟硬體的基本架構和運作原理開始，進而說明網際網路的原理、相關的電腦應用、資訊安全概念及使用網路時應註意之禮節。課程中輔以練習基本電腦應用軟體的操作技能，在修習完本課程後，得以瞭解日後應該如何利用電腦作為輔助自己工作、學業及生活上的工具。

 

BASIC COMPUTER CONCEPTS

Freshman required (2 - 0)

Teaching students start from basic computer structure and operation 
principle of  the software(system software and application software) & 
hardware(CPU, memory, I/O devices). This course will also cover the knowledge of 
networking, information security and the internet moral . The primary goal of 
this course is to make students know how to utilize computer as a tool of work , 
study and normal life in the future.

 

商業套裝軟體 


經一  選修  
(0 - 2)

本課程以介紹Word與Excel使用方法為主，課程內容包括Word的輸入方式、版面設計、表格設計、多媒體文件設計、網頁設計等，以Word製作文件。為了使同學在爾後相關經濟學科，能善用統計工具，Excel著重於資料輸入、建立工作表與圖表等，並以解決問題的角度，以Excel製作圖表，得出解答。

 


SOFEWARE PACKAGE FOR BUSINESS APPLICATION


Freshman elective (0- 2)


This course primarily introduces the usages of Word and Excel. Course topics 
include input, page layout, table, multimedia document, homepage, and creating 
Word document. In order to well use statistical tools in related economics, 
Excel focuses on data input, establishing sheets and figures. In term of solving 
problems, use Excel to create figures for finding solutions. 

 


 

民法概要

經一  選修 
(2 - 2)


本課程之開設，係為指導非法律系之學生，對於民法之基本概念及一般原則，建立正確而實用之觀念。本課程之範圍，包括民法之全部內容，其重點在說明民法與其他法律間之區別與關係，使學生認識五編制的立法結構下，總編則﹙第一條至第一五二條﹚、債編﹙第一五三條至第七五六條﹚、物權編﹙地七五七條至第九六六條﹚、親屬編﹙第九七六條至第一一三七條﹚及繼承編﹙第一一三八條至第一二二五條﹚之規定內容概要。本課程之教學目標，再建立學生對民法的正確觀念，促其註重日常生活與法律規定間之密切關係，進而啟發其對民法專業知識之重視與興趣。

 

INTROCUTION TO CIVIL LAW

Freshman elective (2 - 2)

“INTROCUTION TO CIVIL LAW” is designed to help non-law students 
correctly understand the basic principles of civil law. However, it will be 
emphasized on general vision of the provisions of “General Provisions”, 
“Obligations”, “Property”, “Domestic Relationships” and “Successions” Parts of 
the ROC Civil Code. It is anticipated that the students participating in this 
course will be armed with correct conceptions of civil law, cognizant of the 
close relations of law and daily life, and inspired to value the profession of 
law.


 

個體經濟學

經二  A組 
必修  (3-3)  


本科目主要藉經濟循環流通過程之二部門模式，探討供需與均衡、消費者行為、生產者行為、廠商與市場型態、生產因素市場、一般均衡及福利經濟學等理論。期使學生明瞭消費部門與生產部門間的經濟活動和彼此之間的相互關係，以及如何利用相對價格的功能解決經濟問題。

 

MICROECONOMICS

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)


Microeconomics is study of the circular flow of economic cycle by two sector 
model. It deals with the demand, supply and market equilibrium; consumer’s 
behavior; producer’s behavior; theory of firm and market structure; factor 
markets; general equilibrium theory and welfare economics. This course is 
designed to help students realize the economic activities of the interaction 
between the consumers and producers and know how to solve the economic problems 
by the relative price.


 

個體經濟學

經二  B組 
必修  (3-3) 


本科目主要藉經濟循環流通過程之二部門模式，探討供需與均衡、消費者行為、生產者行為、廠商與市場型態、生產因素市場、一般均衡及福利經濟學,不確定下之經濟行為等理論。學生在明瞭消費部門與生產部門間的經濟活動和彼此間的相互關係之餘，尤應具備應用相關理論解決經濟問題的能力。


 

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)

Based on the circular flow of 
economic behaviors, this course examines topics such as demand, supply, 
equilibrium, consumer choice theory, producer’s behaviors, firms and market 
structures, factor markets, general equilibrium and welfare economics, and 
economic behaviors under uncertainty. In addition to the understanding of the 
interactions between consumer and producer sectors, students are expected to be 
able to solve economic problems via the application of the related theories.


 

個體經濟學

經二  C組 
必修  (3-3)  


本課程主要探討消費者及廠商行為的決策及其影響，課程內容涵蓋消費者選擇、比較靜態分析、價格變動與消費者福利分析、因素市場分析、不同產業結構下之廠商行為分析、市場失靈及政府的角色、一般均衡分析、不確定下的決策分析。

 

MICROECONOMICS

Sophomore required  (3 - 3)

Microeconomics is the study of economic behavior of consumers and 
firms. Specifically, this course focuses on the following topics: consumer 
choice, comparative static analysis, price change and consumer welfare, factor 
markets analysis, firms decisions in various market structures, market failures 
such as externalities, public goods and asymmetric information, general 
equilibrium analysis, choice under uncertainty etc.

 

個體經濟學  


經二  D組 
必修  (3 - 3)  


本科目主要藉經濟循環流通過程之二部門模式，探討供需與均衡、消費者行為、生產者行為、廠商與市場型態、生產因素市場、一般均衡等理論。期使學生明瞭消費部門與生產部門間的經濟活動和彼此之間的相互關係，以及如何利用相對價格的功能解決經濟問題。

 

MICROECONOMICS

Sophomore required  (3 - 3)


Microeconomics is study of the circular flow of economic cycle by two-sector 
model. It deals with the demand, supply and market equilibrium; consumer’s 
behavior; producer’s behavior; theory of firm and market structure; factor 
markets, and general equilibrium theory. This course is designed to help 
students realize the economic activities of the interaction between the 
consumers and producers and know how to solve the economic problems by the 
relative price.


 

貨幣銀行學

經二A  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本課程介紹金融機構與金融市場的功能與運作、以及各種金融工具包含衍生性金融商品、貨幣需求、貨幣供給過程、貨幣政策工具、貨幣政策的執行、IS-LM模型、總合供給與總合需求、貨幣與產出、貨幣政策傳遞機制、通貨膨脹原因與結果。

MONEY AND BANKING

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)


This course introduces the functions and operations of financial institutions 
and markets, financial instruments including derivatives, demand for money, 
money supply process, monetary policy instruments, conduct of monetary policy, 
IS-LM model, aggregate supply and aggregate demand, money and output, channels 
for monetary policy, and causes and consequences of inflation. 


 

貨幣銀行學

經二B、C 
必修  (3 - 3)  

本課程一方面對金融機構與日益重要的金融市場---股票市場、債券市場、外匯市場，以及新的金融工具作逐一的介紹；另一方面則探討中央銀行如何藉貨幣政策的工具，透過金融體系達成其貨幣政策的目標，進而影響一國的總體經濟；最後再探討各種不同的貨幣理論與政策。

MONEY AND BANKING


Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)


This is a course for sophomore. The title of the text is “The Economics of 
Money, Banking, and Financial Markets”. It is written by F. S. Mshkin, the 
excellent professor of Economics at Columbia University. According to his 
introduction of the book, he said, “This book examines how financial markets and 
financial institutions work and explores the role of money in the economy. What 
happens to financial markets, financial institutions, and money is of great 
concern to our politicians and can even have a major impact on our elections. 
The study of money, banking, and financial markets will reward you with an 
understanding of many exciting issues.’


 

統計學

經二  A組 
必修  (3 - 3)  


本課程包括敘述統計與推論統計。前者為簡單之圖表分析；後者包括機率分配、取樣分配、假設檢定、變異數分析、迴歸分析、及卡方配適度檢定。

 


Statistics

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)

This course discusses descriptive 
statistics and inferential statistics. The latter includes probability 
distribution, sampling distribution, hypothesis test, analysis of variance, 
regression, and chi-square test.


 

統計學

經二  B組 
必修  (3 - 3)  


本科目旨在使學生瞭解在不同的目的及不同性質的資料下，如何吸收資料的精華，並根據機率理論作統計分析及推論。講授內容包括：(一)敘述統計；(二)機率、機率分配─統計推論的基礎；(三)推論統計─估計和檢定；(四)無母數分析；(五)變異數分析;（六）迴歸分析。


 


Statistics

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)


    This course equips students with ability to collect and analyze data. It 
teaches students to make inference about population by probability theory. The 
contents include: (1) Descriptive statistics; (2) Probability and probability 
distributions; (3) Statistical inference - estimation and hypothesis testing; 
(4) Nonparametric methods; (5) Analysis of variance;(6) Regression analysis.



 

統計學

經二  C組 
必修  (3 - 3)  


本課程的目標是在介紹基本統計分析所需的觀念與技術，以便商學院學生能應用商學與經濟資料，從事基本的統計分析。本課程的實習課重視MicroSoft 
EXCEL的練習。

 


Statistics

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)

The objective of the courses is 
to study the concepts and analytical skills of basic statistics, so as that the 
students in the College of Business could apply them to a variety of social and 
economic data and thus make statistical and economic analysis for various 
issues. The practical course provided by teaching assistant will emphasize the 
exercises using MicroSoft EXCEL.


 

統計學  


經二  D組 
必修  (3 - 3) 


本課程內容包括敘述統計、機率分配、抽樣分配、統計估計、統計假設檢定、變異數分析、卡方檢定、簡單線性廻歸、複廻歸、無母數統計。

 

STATISTICS

Sophomore  required  (3 - 3)

This course includes descriptive statistics, probability 
distribution, sampling distribution, statistical estimation, hypothesis testing, 
analysis of variance, chi-square tests, simple linear regression, multiple 
regression, and nonparametric statistics.


 

經濟數學  


經二A  選修  
(2 ─ 2)  


數學為分析經濟問題的重要工具，近代經濟理論的蓬勃發展得力於數理工具的運用。本課程旨在教導學生，如何以嚴謹而客觀的數理方法去分析與研究經濟問題，以增進對經濟問題的瞭解。主要講授內容為：基本概念、單變數微積分與最適化分析、線性代數、多變數微積分、多變數的最適化分析、有限制的最適化分析以及比較靜態分析。


 


MATHEMATICS FOR ECONOMICS

Sophomore  Required  (2 ─ 2)

Mathematics is an important 
analytical tool to help us understand and handle with economic problems.  The 
development of modern economic theories relies heavily on this tool.  The 
purpose of this course is to enhance students’ ability to study economics by 
using a rigorously mathematical method.  The topics covered in this course are 
Fundamentals, Univariate Calculus and Optimization, Linear Algebra, Calculus for 
Multivariate Functions, Optimization of Multivariate Functions, Constrained 
Optimization, and Comparative Static Analysis.


 

經濟數學  


經二B、C 
選修  (2 ─ 2)  


凡是現代研究經濟學的同學均需要某些數學的輔助，建立模型以分析經濟事務。數學不僅提供一種嚴謹而簡潔的工具，也有助於對複雜經濟問題及理論的瞭解。本課程主要以數學為主，經濟為輔，書中列舉許許多多經濟學範例以供初學者參考，希望能提供同學瞭解如何使用數學以解決經濟問題。


 


MATHEMATICS FOR ECONOMICS

Sophomore  Required  (2 ─ 2)


This is a course for sophomore. The title of the text is “Fundamental Methods of 
Mathematical Economics”. It is written by A. C. Chiang, the excellent professor 
of Economics at University of Connecticut. According to his preface of the book, 
he said, “This book is written for those students of economics intent on 
learning the basic mathematical methods that have become indispensable for a 
proper understanding of the current economic literature.

 

企業管理  


經二  選修  
(3 - 0)


企業管理以管理功能為課程主軸，另以企業功能為輔，期使修讀同學瞭解企業運作的原理以及企業管理的重要議題。管理功能講授內容包括計劃、組織、領導、控制等單元，企業功能講授內容則以人力資源、行銷、財務、資訊以及作業管理等單元之概要理論為主，課程參酌相關實例及個案，使學習者得以瞭解理論運用於實務，建立管理實務之觀念。


 

BUSINESS MANAGEMENT 

Sophomore  elective  (3 - 0)

The purpose of this course is to familiarize the students with 
basic modern management concepts and important issues of business operation. The 
topics introduced are (1) the evolution of management thought; (2) the 
management process include - planning, organizing, staffing, leading and 
controlling;  (3) the future of management theory and challenge;  (4) the 
business function which include human resources, marketing, financing and MIS.

 


金融管理

經二 
選修  (2 - 2)  


本課程之主要內容為簡介金融機構功能及其風險管理。在金融機構功能方面，依序討論銀行業、保險業、證券業、投資銀行業、投信業等各種金融機構之業務內容及監理機制；在風險管理方面，則討論金融機構面臨之各項風險（利率風險、市場風險、信用風險、作業風險及流動性風險等）及管理風險之具體方法。

 

Financial Institutions Management

Sophomore  elective  (2 - 2)

This course focuses on overview of main activities and risk 
management of financial institutions. Firstly, we will introduce the main 
products and services provided by financial institutions such as banks, 
insurance companies, securities firms, investment banks, mutual fund companies 
and finance companies. Secondly, we will discuss risks faced by these 
institutions, which are interest rate risk, market risk, credit risk, 
operational risk and liquidity risk. Finally, we will introduce some tools to 
measure and manage those risks effectively.


 

商事法

經二  選修  
(2 -2)


本課程乃在於介紹商事法之基礎理論及商事法內含之各該法律。本課程包含四個部份，即公司法、票據法、海商法及保險法。由於社會之經濟活動愈頻繁，通曉商事法實有其必要，同學藉由此課程之學習，俾使瞭解商事法之內涵以及各該法律之具體規範與適用，以其同學能學以致用。

 

BUSINESS  LAW

Sophomore  elective  (2 - 2)

This course introduces basic 
theory of the Commercial Law. Commercial Law cautions four parts, Company Law; 
Law of Bills and Notes(Negotiable Interments); Maritime Law of Insurance. In 
society economic action is more and more, so the student is need to know the 
Commercial Law what it is. By learning this course, the students will realize 
the Commercial Law and its scope of application indeed and take advantages of it 
in the future.


 

投資理論與實務 


經二  選修  
(2 - 2)  


本課程旨在對於投資學領域作一全盤性介紹，包括股票、債券、期貨、選擇權等投資商品之理論與實務，範圍包括國內市場及國際市場。課程內容先教授各投資商品之特性，其次，各投資商品之市場交易實務及遊戲規則，接著教授市場價格決定的各種模型，最後為分析影響投資商品價格的因素及適當的買賣時機，期使學生除了理論，也重視實務，並從教授實際投資個案、事件及學術實證成果，啟發學生對投資商品的邏輯思考，能將知識與經驗合一，獲得整體之觀念，而有助於進一步研究或將來從事工商業工作。

 

THEORY & PRACTICE OF INVESTMENT

Sophomore elective  (2-2)

The aim of the course is to introduce the theory and practice of 
investment comprehensively, including the theory and practice of securities, 
foreign exchanges, futures and options. I take a unified approach to each by 
answering these questions：What are the essential 
features of the instrument？How is the instrument 
bought and sold and how does the market for the instrument operate？ 
What are the basic determinants of investment value？The 
course offers the theoretical analysis method and practice to help students to 
develop an overall concept of investment and to understand the characteristics 
of all kinds of investment commodities.

 

財務經濟學  


經二  選修  
(2 -2)  

本課程的目標是在探討現代企業經理人(financial 
manager)所面臨的投資決策(investment decision)與融資決策(financing 
decision)課題，兼具理論與實務。除介紹一般財務管理的內容外，並包括資本市場行為、運作及企業經濟活動有關的內容。


FINANCIAL ECONOMICS

Sophomore  elective  (2-2)

The objective of the course is to study the investment decisions 
and financing decisions faced by the financial managers in modern corporations. 
It will be concerned with not only financial theories but also practical issues. 
The course will cover general financial topics as well as the behaviors of 
capital markets and the economic activities of modern corporations.


 

財務管理  


經二  選修（2-2）

課程目的：


1.            

激發學習財務知識的興趣


2.            

連結財務領域與其他經濟學領域的知識


3.            

探討財務決策的基本觀念與理論


4.            

將財務的基本理論與觀念運用於解決企業之實務問題


 


FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT 


