Arouse the interests of learning 
Finance.


2.            

Help building the linkages 
between Finance and Economics.


3.            

Explore the concepts and theories 
of financial decisions making.


4.            

Help applying the theories 
learned to handle the real world financial problems.


 

證券投資分析與實務

經二 選修 （2-2） 



(一)教學目標


已修習過經濟學原理→修畢本課程『證券投資分析與實務』(實務為主、理論為輔)→瞭解證券投資工具(股票市場及債券市場為主)之意義、重要性、分析技巧及投資個案之實務→一方面有益同學未來證券投資相關工作之尋找、一方面有助個人投資理財之規劃。


(二)教學方向


股票投資分析實務方面：自基本面、政策面、資金面、市場面、產業面、個股面、技術面(所謂面面俱到)，去綜合探討股票市場。


債券投資分析實務方面：深入探討總經分析，以期準確預測利率走勢(因為債券投資成敗全在利率之研判)。


 

The stock investment and the practical


Sophomore  elective  (2-2)

Teaching Target:


People who have already studied the economics principle 
→Finish 
this curriculum, which is『The stock investment and the 
practical』(practical first, then the theory )→Well 
know the meaning, importance of the stock investment tool (stock market and 
bonds market at first), analyze the technique and invest the individual cases 
practiced →on one side it helps the related work in 
the future, on the other side it helps the programming of personal investment 
and finance.

Pedagogy: 


Stock investment analysis is to probe into the 
stock market based on influence of fundamental aspect, political aspect, market 
aspect, industry aspect, stock aspect, and technical aspect.


Bond market 
analysis, to go deep into macro 
economic analysis and forecast the interest rate in the future(the success of 
investment will all be depending on the direction of interest rate). 


 

廠商決策理論與應用 


經二  選修 
(2/2)  


希望可透過此一門課程讓同學們瞭解並學得「制訂決策」的重點與技巧，除此之外，更希望同學們學得團隊合作的精神與應有的正確態度與價值觀。此課程主要是欲探討「廠商決策的重點與技巧」，其內容大致為以下幾點：


（一）     

在現今不確定性高且又複雜的環境下，廠商該如何做出正確的經營管理決策呢？又該如何避免掉入錯誤決策的陷阱呢？


（二）     
如何檢視「思考架構」呢？


（三）     
「組織分工」的重要性


（四）     
垂直與水平兩種思考模式該如何交互運用呢？

在（一）與（二）中大致上是運用一些統計、經濟的基礎概念再加上幾篇實用的文章作為理論的架構，然後再試著將理論與實務作結合與應用。

 

Decision 
Marketing under Uncertainty Model and Choice

Sophomore elective  (2-2)

By this course we hope students 
can learn and understand the important points and skills of 
「how 
to make strategies」. Beside this, we hope students can 
learn more about the spirit of teamwork, and train the correct attitude and 
values in the learning process. This course is to discuss 「how 
to make strategies of companies」. Its content is 
roughly the following：（一）How do companies plan correct 
strategies of management in the environment of high uncertain and complex 
condition? How to avoid falling in traps of making wrong strategies?（二）How 
to review 「the structure of thought」?（三）The 
important concepts and principle of 「the division of 
organization management」（四）How to apply mutually with 
both vertical thought model and horizontal thought model?  In the sections of
（一）and（二）, we roughly use 
some base concepts of statistics and economics, and increase some practical 
articles to be the structure of theory, then we try to combine and apply with 
the theory and practical cases.


 

財經英文會話

經二 選修 （2- 0） 

課程目的：


這門課程的主要目的是在讓學生練習在一般商業場合中所使用的各種口頭會話及其型式。其中包括五個主要領域：社交、電話、會議、商業促銷以及談判。而這門課並不要求學生有特殊的商業知識，而是純粹要加強學生對於聽與說的技巧。而課程中將包括一個由2~3個學生一組的上臺報告。

 

Business 
Conversation [for Economics Majors]

Sophomore elective  (2-0)


Course Objective:


The purpose of the class is to let students practice using the types of English 
oral structures that are commonly used in business. The five key areas that will 
be covered are: Socializing, Telephoning, Meetings, Making Business 
Presentations, and Negotiating. No special knowledge of business terms or 
concepts is required as the course will focus on improving the students’ 
speaking and listening skills. There will be one presentation that will be done 
in groups of 2 – 3 students.

 

財經英文閱讀

經二 選修 （0/2） 


課程目的：


學生再課堂中將學習到一般使用於商業文章的字彙及其表示方式。學生再課堂中需研讀一些商業文章（如經濟學人、華爾街日報、The 
Financial Times等）。而閱讀的主題本身將著重在一些有趣的商業及經濟議題如投資、實質資產市場、品牌、商業規範以及金融歷史等。


而課程計畫將包括針對一間公司的產業情況以及歷史等作出一個完整的報告以及參與一個線上的股票市場模擬遊戲等。

 

Business Reading [for Economics Majors]

Sophomore elective  (0-2)


Course Purpose:


Students will learn English vocabulary and expressions as commonly used in the



business press. Extensive reading of the business press [The Economist, The 
Wall Street Journal, The Financial Times, etc.]  will be required of 
students. Readings will focus on topically interesting business and economic 
issues such as investments, the real estate market, branding, business ethics, 
financial history, etc. Projects / assignments may include following one company 
and its industry throughout the term and making a major report/presentation on 
it and participating in an on-line stock market game.

 

財經資料庫應用分析

經二 選修 （0/2） 



本課程開設目標是為幫助學生，利用經濟與財務資料庫，應用在實務的日常生活與社會面之經濟財務分析。本課程內容將含蓋（1）重要財經資料庫的介紹與使用；（2）各項基本的與深入的經濟財務事務或課題的應用分析（主要指統計分析）；及（3）Excel統計功能與簡單統計軟體的介紹與使用。整學期的上課都是在電腦教室。


 


Application and Analysis of Economic and Financial Databases


Sophomore elective  (0-2)


The course is designed to fit the purpose that students know how to utilize the 
major economic and financial databases and to apply the simple statistical 
techniques to various practical economic and financial issues (either personal 
or social ones). The course will cover the following tasks: 1) Learn to use the 
major economic and financial databases; 2) Apply the simple statistical 
procedures to various practical economic and financial issues; and 3) Learn to 
use the Excel’s statistical functions and other simple statistical software. The 
class will be proceeded in the classroom with computer and multimedia 
apparatuses.


 

總體經濟學

經三  A、D組 
必修 (3/3)  


透過簡單的總體經濟模型觀察一個經濟體系的經濟活動，分析景氣循環的原因及其與經濟體系內一些重要的變數，如失業率、通貨膨脹率間之關連。主要的課題包括：國民所得，物價水準，失業，通貨膨脹，政府政策，國際貿易以及經濟成長等。


Macroeconomics


Junior required (3-3)

This course is to understand 
economic activies in an aggregate level of an economy, such as a nation, by 
establishing a macroeconomic model.  The main topics include national product, 
price level, unemployment, inflation, economic policies, economics growth, and 
international trade.


 

總體經濟學 

經三  C組 必修 
(3 - 3) 


本科目旨在探討總體經濟中最重要的問題：失業、物價膨脹以及經濟成長的決定因素，並對政府總體經濟政策效果加以評估。課程並著重經濟個體的理性行為介紹。講授內容包括：


•國民所得會計


•經濟個體在商品、勞動與資產市場中的理性行為分析

•經濟成長理論（新古典與內生成長模型）


•景氣循環理論（包括古典、凱因斯、貨幣及新古典學派等） 


•通貨膨脹與失業問題

Macroeconomics


Junior  required  (3-3)


   This course discusses the determinants of important macroeconomics topics – 
unemployment, inflation and economic growth. Different government macroeconomic 
policies are evaluated by different macroeconomic theory. 


In addition, the rational behaviors of economic agents in different markets are 
emphasized and introduced as foundations for macroeconomic analysis. The 
contents of this course are


(1)         
National income accounting


(2)         
Rational behavior of economic 
agents in labor, goods and assets markets


(3)         
Economic growth theory 
(neo-classical and endogenous growth models)


(4)         
Business cycle theory (classical, 
Keynesian, new classical and new Keynesian models)


(5)         
Unemployment and inflation


 

總體經濟學 


經三  C組 
必修  


本課程擬對總體經濟學提出一個具有系統的說明，此為兩學期總體經濟理論的課程。


第一學期要討論的議題如下：

第一部分：總體經濟之介紹與測度


1.        
總體經濟簡介


2.        
總體經濟測度


3.        
景氣循環測度

第二部分：單期的總體經濟模型


4.        
消費者與廠商行為：工作與休閒


5.        
單期的封閉總體經濟模型

第三部分：經濟成長


6.        
經濟成長：馬爾薩斯與梭羅


7.        
內生成長中國家的所得不均

 


第二學期要討論的議題如下：

第四部分：儲蓄、政府赤字和投資


8.        
兩期模型：消費與儲蓄的選擇與李嘉圖對等定理


9.        
投資的實質跨期模型

第五部分：貨幣與景氣循環


10.     

貨幣的跨期模型：貨幣中立性


11.     

景氣循環的市場結清模型


12.     

凱因斯景氣循環理論：工資僵固模型

第六部分：國際總體經濟學


13.     

資產與商品的國際交易


14.     

開放經濟的貨幣

 

Macroeconomics


Junior  required  (3-3)

The course offers a systematic 
analysis of macroeconomics. It is a two-semester sequence in macroeconomic 
theory. 


The topics covered in the first semester include：

Part I  Introduction and 
Measurement Issues


1.        
Introduction


2.        
Measurement


3.        
Business cycle measurement

Part II  A One-Period Model of 
the Macroeconomy


4.        
Consumer and firm behavior: the 
work-leisure


5.        
A closed-economy one-period 
macroeconomic model

Part III  Economic Growth


6.        
Economic growth: Malthus and 
Solow


7.        
Income disparity among countries 
and endogenous growth


 


The topics covered in the second semester include：

Part IV  Savings, Government 
Deficits and Investment


8.        
A two-period model: the 
consumption-savings decision and Ricardian Equivalence


9.        
A real intertemporal model with 
investment

Part V  Money and Business Cycles


10.     
A monetary intertemporal model: the neutrality of money


11.     
Market-clearing models of the business cycle


12.     
Keynesian business cycle theory: the sticky wage model

Pare VI  International 
Macroeconomics


13.     
International trade in goods and assets


14.     
Money in the open economy


 

財政學

經三A  必修  
(3-3)  


本學科旨在探討在混合式經濟體系下公共部門之經濟學，內容所涵蓋之範圍不僅包括公共收入之籌集，而且涉及公共支出對資源配置、所得分配與經濟穩定之影響。對各項問題之探討同時兼顧實質面與貨幣面之衝擊，公司兩部門間之交互作用、剖析公共收支對民間部門之影響，若無公共部門之介入則私經濟部門又將如何運作﹖

PUBLIC FINANCE


Junior  required  (3-3)

The discipline deals with the 
economics of the public sector as that sector operates in a mixed system. Its 
operation includes not only financing but bas broad bearing on the level and 
allocation of resource use, the distribution of income, and the level of 
economic activity. Although our subject matter is traditionally referred to as 
public finance, the book thus deals with the real as well as the financial 
aspects of the problem. The public sector operates in interaction with the 
private, both sectors enter the analysis. Not only do the effects of expenditure 
and fax policies depend upon the reaction of the private sector, but the need 
for fiscal measures is determined by how the private sector would perform in 
their absence.


 

財政學

經三B  必修  
(3-3)  


財政學主要在探討政府部門的稅收與支出之活動，及其對個人經濟行為之影響、資源之重新配置以及所得重分配之一門學科。本課程包括如下之主題：福利經濟學之分析架構、公共財、外部性、政治經濟、所得重分配之理論、低收入戶之補助、年金、失業保險、健康保險、成本收益分析、稅收與所得重分配、稅收之效率性與公平性、個人所得稅、公司稅、消費稅、財富稅、以及政府債務等。

PUBLIC FINANCE


Junior  required  (3-3)


Public finance is a course about the taxing and spending activities of 
government. Our focus is on the microeconomic functions of government, the way 
government affects the allocation of resources and the distribution of income. 
This course covers the following subjects: tools of positive analysis, tools of 
normative analysis, public goods, externalities, political economy, income 
redistribution: conceptual issues, expenditure programs for the poor, social 
insurance : social security, unemployment insurance, and health care, 
cost-benefit analysis, taxation and income distribution, taxation and 
efficiency, efficient and equitable taxation, the personal income tax, personal 
taxation and behavior, the corporation tax, deficit finance, taxes on 
consumption and wealth.


 

財政學

經三C  必修  
(3-3)  


本學科旨在探討在混合式經濟體系下公共部門之經濟學，內容所涵蓋之範圍不僅包括公共收入之籌集，而且涉及公共支出對資源配置、所得分配與經濟穩定之影響。對各項問題之探討同時兼顧實質面與貨幣面之衝擊，公司兩部門間之交互作用、剖析公共收支對民間部門之影響，若無公共部門之介入則私經濟部門又將如何運作﹖

PUBLIC FINANCE


