經濟思想史 


經三A、B 
 必修 (2-2)  


經濟思想史旨在探討西方經濟思潮的形成，從前現代政治經濟學延伸至當代經濟學，涵蓋主要的經濟思想家以及各種不同的思想學派，包括主流及非主流學派。使用教材為最新的中英文論文及專書。


HISTORY OF ECONOMIC THOUGHT


Junior  required  (2-2)


This course introduces the sources and factors that drive the evolution of 
modern western economic thoughts. It starts from the pre-modern political 
economy and persists to the contemporary economics. It covers primary great 
economists as well as main schools in the history of economic thought, including 
orthodox and heterodox doctrines. The textbook will be updated English textbook.


 

經濟思想史 


經三C
必修 (2-2)  


一、教學目標


讓學生瞭解，（一）每一個時期經濟學家的經濟思想，都是繼承了前輩所創造的成果和留下來的思想精髓；（二）資本主義經濟思想的發達因素和基本特色。


二、課程內容


本課程以歷史的觀點，有系統地探討西方國家許多重要的經濟學家在經濟思想上的貢獻。另外，對現代主要經濟學家的理論及其思想淵源亦做深度的介紹，俾便學生夠從中獲得經濟思想史方面的基本理論、主要內容和研究方法。


三、實施方式


    

指定一本具有條理、有系統的教科書，依照預定進度講授各經濟學說產生的歷史背景、社會環境及詳細內容；另一方面於教科書的每一章指定專題討論，經由師生的深入互動，深化學生對於學習重點的瞭解，及訓練其分析與整合思考的能力，進而達成本課程之教學目標。


 


HISTORY OF ECONOMIC THOUGHT


Junior  required  (2-2)  Lecturer: Chun-Long Chen, Associate Professor

＊Objectives:

To enable students be aware of 
1.economists’ economic thought in each period inherits the essence and outputs 
created from their seniors; 2. factors that capitalism economic thought prosper 
and its characteristics.

＊Contents:

Based on historical point of 
view, the course discusses systematically many crucial economists’ economic 
thought in the western countries. In addition, there are also in-depth 
introductions on modern economists’ theory and origins. In this way, students 
can acquire knowledge on basic economic theory, major contents and research 
method. 

＊Implementation 
measures:

Through measures of assigning a 
textbook with systematic and logical descriptions and lecturing related detailed 
content, historical background and social environment of each economic thought 
according to syllabus, as well as students’ group discussion on assigned topics 
in each chapter, the course will be well implemented and objectives will be 
achieved. 


 

區域經濟學  


經三  選修  
(2 -2)  


區域經濟學乃把「空間」視為一個向度去重新檢視經濟議題的科目，探討決定經濟活動在空間分佈的因素及其改變所產生的影響。本課程乃區域經濟學的入門。授課內容包括區位理論、聚集經濟、空間定價、都市體系、區域成長、地租、都市土地使用、土地使用管制、住宅問題、都市交通問題等。


 


REGIONAL ECONOMICS


Junior  Elective  (2 -2)

Regional Economics is to treat “space” as a 
dimension to re-examine the issues in economics. This course is to identify the 
factors governing the distribution of economic activities over space and to 
explore the consequences when these factors changes. This course is an 
introduction to regional economics, exploring the distribution of economic 
activities over space. The topics to be covered in the course are Location 
Theory, Agglomeration Economies, Spatial Pricing Theory, Urban Systems, Regional 
Growth, Urban Land Use, Land Use Control, Housing Issues, and Urban 
Transportation Problems.


 

福利經濟學  

經三 
選修  (2-2)


福利經濟學主要研究經濟資源的最適配置，尤其對經濟政策的抉擇更提供理論之基礎，以使社會資源作更有效的運用，避免資源配置失當與浪費。本課程分兩部分：(1)說明福利經濟之概念與衡量方法的理論基礎。(2)分析公共政策的福利效果。

 

Welfare Economics

Junior  elective  (2-2)

Welfare Economics is study of optimum allocation of economic 
resources.  It covers part of economic theory that deals with the problem of 
defining “What is good for the society” and it is also helpful to the economic 
policy concerned with determining the maximum well-being for the society. This 
course includes two parts:(1) Explain the fundamental principles of welfare 
economics and the methods of measuring the social welfare. (2) Analyze the 
welfare effects of public policy.


 

高等統計學

經三  選修  
(2 - 2)  


本課程使大三大四學生能更進一步瞭解機率理論及統計推論，並進而學習如何運用統計方法來作分析研究。內容包含：機率理論及各種機率分配、樣本分配理論、未知母體參數之推估方法及其性質、統計檢定方法、線性迴歸模型分析及其推估方法。


Advanced Statistics

Junior  elective  (2-2)


"The intent of the course is to provide junior or senior students in economic 
department with advanced knowledge in probability theory and statistical 
inference.

This course will cover the 
following areas: empirical and probability distribution, probability, discrete 
distribution, continuous distribution, multivariable distribution, sampling 
distribution theory, estimation, tests of statistical hypotheses and the theory 
of statistical inference.


 

計量經濟學  


經三  A組 
選修  (2 - 2)  


本科目旨在介紹計量經濟理論及其應用，使學生瞭解如何利用統計學的迴歸分析從事經濟理論的實證分析。講授內容包括：(1)統計相關理論的複習 
(2)單一方程式模型之設定、估計及推論，並討論模型各樣基本假設不能滿足時的解決方法；(3)如何運用電子計算機來作各種估計和預測。


ECONOMETRICS

Junior elective  (2-2)


The objective of this course is to introduce the basic econometric theory and 
its applications so that the students know how to analyze economic problems with 
regression analysis. It’ll cover (1) a review of some relevant statistics (2) 
the specification, estimation and prediction of single equation models, and the 
solutions to violations of some basic assumptions. (3) application of software 
package to make estimations and predictions of econometric models.


 

計量經濟學  


經三  B組 
選修  (2 - 2)  


本科目旨在介紹計量經濟理論及其應用，使學生瞭解如何利用統計學的迴歸分析從事經濟理論的實證分析。講授內容包括：(1)單一方程式模型之設定、估計及推論，並討論模型各樣基本假設不能滿足時的解決方法；(2)聯立方程式模型之簡單介紹。教學時除著重計量方法之分析和解釋外，也指導學生運用電子計算機來作各種估計和預測。


ECONOMETRICS

Junior  elective  (2-2)


The objective of this course is to introduce the basic econometric theory and 
its applications so that the students know how to analyze economic problems with 
regression analysis. It’ll cover (1) the specification, estimation and 
prediction of single equation models, and the solutions to violations of some 
basic assumptions. (2) Introduction of the simultaneous models (3) application 
of software package to make estimations and predictions of econometric models.


 

 

數理經濟學  


經三  選修  
(3 ─ 3)  


本科目旨在訓練學生進階的數學分析經濟學的能力，重點以經濟動態分析方法為主。講授內容包括積分與經濟的應用、線性一階差分方程式、非線性一階差分方程式、線性二階差分方程式、線性一階微分方程式、非線性一階微分方程式、線性二階微分方程式、差分與微分的聯立方程式、最適控制理論。

 

MATHEMATICAL ECONOMICS

Junior  Elective  (2 ─ 2)

The objective of this course is to enhance the students’ ability to 
analyze economics using advanced mathematical method. The topics to be covered 
in the course are Integration and Economics Applications, Linear, First-Order 
Difference Equations, Nonlinear First-Order Difference Equations, Linear 
Second-Order Difference Equations, Linear First-Order Differential Equations, 
Nonlinear First-Order Differential Equations, Linear Second-Order Differential 
Equations, Simultaneous Systems of Differential and Difference Equations, and 
Optimal Control Theory.


 


經濟專題討論 (A)  

經三 選修（2-0） 


經濟專題討論(A)主要在探討「進口救濟制度--國際貿易政策與產業競爭策略」，瞭解WTO（世界貿易組織）組織架構及其運作，探討我國加入WTO最新進展及影響評估與因應對策，進口救濟制度實施之意義、沿革及其發展，我國平衡稅及反傾銷稅與進口救濟制度之運作方式及採行貿易或產業調整協助等救濟措施之規範，與WTO之反傾銷協定、補貼及平衡措施協定與防衛條款有關之最新發展作有系統介紹，期能瞭解我國在打開全球國家（地區）之市場管道之同時，抵制國際保護主義壓力對國內受害產業提供適度之暫時性「安全閥」救濟工具之運用，作為理論與實務兼修之入階，藉以瞭解國家經濟政策運作方向，期能將來進入社會服務貢獻所學。


 


Economic Special Topic (I) 

Junior  elective  
（2-0）

The main objective of Economic Special Topics (I) “International 
Trade Policy and Industrial Competition strategy” is to Understand the organic 
structure and its operation of World Trade Organization (WTO) comprehensive 
scope will definitely hasten the trade liberalization process and facilitate 
world trade in the future. It is possible that some domestic industries may face 
stringent competition from foreign counterparts. In general the current import 
relief program of Taiwan is consistent with WTO principles, although there are 
some procedures which need to be altered. The direction of future modifications 
in Taiwan’s safeguard provisions and antidumping & countervailing duties. 
Consequently, an import relief is required to the function as temporary “safe 
values” to alleviate the shock of trade liberalization. It could hopefully 
provide an environment in which injured domestic industries are able to make 
some structural adjustments so as to compete with foreign businesses. We hope 
creat could though this training program which contribution to our society.

 


經濟專題討論 (B) 

經三 
選修（0-2）  


我國已正式加入世界貿易組織（WTO），「經濟專題討論(II)--國際貿易政策與產業競爭策略」主要在探討美國、歐盟、澳洲、加拿大、中國大陸、韓國、日本、越南、紐西蘭、菲律賓、印尼等主要國家之進口救濟制度與實義，及其與我國與世界貿易組織烏拉圭回合協定下主要貿易國之制度作乙比較，期能瞭解各國進口救濟制度在貿易自由化政策發展過程中所扮演「安全閥」及促進產業轉移調整的角色，進而能建立一套國內法中客觀可行之運行程序及合理救濟制度，減少對貿易流量造成扭曲，使市場競爭更趨公平合理。

 

Economic Special Topics (II) 

Junior  elective  
（0-2）

We have joined the World Trade Organization（WTO）The 
establishment of an import relief system that abide by WTO agreement is the 
right and duty of any WTO contracting party. This course is aimed at studying 
the International Trade Policy changed which affected industrial competition 
Strategy Also, we compare the safeguards law and practice of USA, EU, Australia, 
Canada, Mainland China, Korea, Japan, Vietnan, Newzealand, phillippine, 
Indonesia as well as the rule of WTO safeguards agreement, so as to understand 
the “safety valve” and industry adjustment roles under safeguards system of each 
country in the free trade environment. Eventually, we will reduce trade flow an 
applicable and suitable import relief system, which cause distortion and 
maintains a fair trade circumstance.

 

賽局理論與應用

經三  選修  
(2 ─ 2)  

本課程介紹賽局論的基礎觀念，主要內容包括：一.靜態完全資訊--策略式賽局之定義，耐許均衡，混合策略，以及經濟應用例子：囚犯困境、投票賽局等。二.靜態不完全資訊—貝氏賽局，策略及貝氏耐許均衡，應用：拍賣與投標，唐榮案例。三.動態完全資訊：詳盡式賽局，定義與策略，序列理性，反向歸納與子賽局完美均衡，重複賽局與長期合作關係，動態廠商行為賽局。四.動態不完全資訊賽局：一致信念與貝氏完美均衡，傳訊賽局，代理人賽局。

 

The Theories and Application of Game 
Theory

Junior elective (2 - 2)

This course introduces basic 
definitions and concept of game theory. I. Static complete information—Strategic 
form game: Nash equilibrium, mixed strategy and economic applications: 
prisoners’ dilemma game, voting game. II. Static incomplete information—Bayesian 
game: strategy and Bayesian Nash equilibrium, applications including auction and 
bidding, case study of Teng-Eng Iron Company. III. Dynamic complete 
information—extensive form game: definition and strategy, sequential 
rationality, backward induction and subgame perfect Nash equilibrium, repeated 
game and long term cooperation, dynamic firm behavior. IV. Dynamic incomplete 
information game: consistent belief and perfect Bayesian equilibrium, signaling 
game , principal agent game.

 

消費者行為研究

經三  選修  
(2 - 2)  


希望透過此一門課程可讓同學們學習，如何藉著瞭解消費者心目中的認知與偏好，進而擬訂廠商的行銷策略；並藉著分析現今消費者行為實際個案，讓同學們不僅可以活用理論且亦能夠瞭解消費行為與市場的動向，訓練同學們從外而內的思考方式。除此之外，更希望同學們能學得團隊合作的精神與應有的正確態度與價值觀。其內容大致如下：（一）廠商實際個案市場定位分析（二）消費者行為類型分析（三）產品組合分析（四）行銷研究多變量分析（五）市場機會缺口分析。

 


Consumer’s Behavior Study

Junior elective (2 - 2)

By this course we hope students 
can learn how to know the sense and the preference of consumers in mind, then 
decide the company's marketing strategy further. By analyzing the practical case 
of consumer's behavior, students not only apply theories in the practical case 
but also know more about the consumer's behavior and the trend of market. To 
train the students how to use the thinking method from outside into inside. 
Beside this, we hope students can learn more about the spirit of teamwork, and 
train the correct attitude and values in the learning process.  Its content is 
roughly the following：

（一）Analysis 
Market Position by Manufacturer's Practical Case

（二）Analysis 
the Perception and Preference by Customers' Behavior Model

（三）Analysis 
Products Mix by BCG Model

（四）Marketing 
Research by Multi-Variation Analysis

（五）Analysis the Gap by Marketing Opportunity 
Model

 

經濟法規 (A) (B)

經三  選修  
(2/0)(0/2)


經濟法規乃架構在以國民全體經濟利益為最高指導原則下，強化企業經濟活動之運作，以求增進全民福祉。


本課程分上、下兩學期，教授項目包括銀行法、公平交易法、消費者保護法及智慧財產權法等與經濟相關之法規範。

ECONOMIC REGULATIONS (A) (B)

Junior elective (2 - 0) (0 - 2)

The framework of Economic Laws is mainly focesing on the economic 
interests of people live in the society. Through regulation on the coporations’ 
economic activities so as to two semesters, including Banking Law, Anti-trust 
Law, consumer protection Law, Patern Law, Trademark Law, Copyright Law and any 
other regulations related to economic affairs.

 


財務經濟專題研究

經三  選修  
(2 － 2)  


本課程接續「財務經濟學」課程，為有興趣於財務、投資理論的同學，提供專題式與較深入的研討，主要上課內容為選擇權與期貨。本課程並將提供利用電腦統計軟體與台灣財務資料庫的實作與應用。


Topics in Financial Economics

