教育經濟與政策
經三 選修 (0/3) 
本門課主要的目標在培育學生對人力與教育資源分配及教育政策等問題之分析能力。我們希望從經濟學的角度來分析教育之多面向，包括教育之市場、成本、投資、消費、經費、規模及資源分配等課題，課堂中並將對相關之教育政策加以剖析。
　

Educational Economics and policy
Junior Elective (0/3)
The main goal of this course is to cultivate student’s ability on analyzing 
human and educational resource allocation as well as educational policies. We 
hope to investigate the multiple dimensions of education from the perspective of 
economist. The topics of this course will cover educational market, cost, 
investment, consumption, scale and resource allocation. Contemporary educational 
policies will also be analyzed in the class.

兩岸經貿關係專題討論
經四 選修 （3/0）
兩岸經貿關係是台灣經濟發展的關鍵影響因素。本課程以專題討論方式協助學生瞭解兩岸經貿發展的趨勢及相關課題，課程內容涵蓋：
1. 中國大陸經濟趨勢及對台灣的影響
2. 兩岸經貿發展及相關課題
3. 兩岸貿易及台商大陸投資
4. 兩岸協商與兩岸經貿關係正常化
5. 兩岸經濟合作架構協議（ECFA）相關課題
6. 兩岸經貿關係發展的非經濟因素
　

Topics on Cross-Strait Economic 
Relations 
Senior Elective (3/0)
The cross-strait economic relations are the most decisive influence on Taiwan’s 
economic development. This course is designed to assist students to understand 
the trends of cross-strait economic relations and related issues. Followings are 
contents of this course:
1. The trend of China’s economy and its impact on Taiwan
2. The development of cross-strait economic relations and related issues
3. The cross-strait trade and Taiwanese investment in China
4. Cross-strait negotiations and normalization on cross-strait economic 
relations
5. Related issues on ECFA (Cross-Strait Economic Cooperation Framework 
Agreement) 
6. Non-economic factors behind cross-strait economic relations
　

國際經濟學  


經四A  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本課程講授國際經濟學重要理論及當前國際金融問題，包括國際貿易理論與政策，及國際金融兩部分，前者涵蓋國際貿易理論、經濟成長與國際貿易、貿易政策，後者涵蓋國際收支平衡表、外匯市場、匯率的決定理論、固定匯率與浮動匯率制度下的總體經濟政策、開放經濟體系物價與產出、最適通貨區域、國際金融市場與工具，以及國際貨幣制度。

 

INTERNATIONAL ECONOMICS


Senior  required  (3-3)

This course provides the major theories in international economics 
and current international financial issues. It comprises international trade 
theory and policy, and international finance. The former covers the 
international trade theories, economic growth and international trade, and 
international trade policy. The latter covers balance of payments account, 
foreign exchange market, exchange rates determination, macroeconomic policy 
under the fixed and flexible exchange system, output and price in the open 
economy, optimum currency area, international financial markets and instruments, 
and current international monetary arrangements. 


 

 

國際經濟學  


經四B、C 
必修  (3 ─ 3)  


本課程旨在講授國際經濟學重要理論及問題，期使學生瞭解並評估國際經濟現況。教學內容包括國際貿易與國際金融兩部分，其中國際貿易討論國際貿易理論、經濟成長與國際貿易、貿易政策，國際金融則探討外匯市場、匯率的決定、浮動匯率制度下的總體經濟政策與調整、最適通貨區域與歐洲經驗、國際資本市場、開發中國家債務問題等主題。此外，如何將國際經濟理論應用在現實主要國際經濟問題之分析亦是本課程主要特色之一。

INTERNATIONAL ECONOMICS


Senior  required  (3-3)

    This course mainly provides the most important theories and an 
up-to-date analytical framework on international economics for illuminating 
current events.  It is divided into two halves, a one-semester course on trade 
theory and a one-semester course on international monetary economics.

    The course on trade theory covers international trade theories, 
economic growth and international economics, international trade policy.

    International monetary economics covers several topics 
including (1)exchange rates and the foreign exchange market, (2) exchange rates 
determination, (3)macroeconomic policy and coordination under floating exchange 
rates, (4)optimum currency areas and the European experience, (5)global capital 
market, (6)debt problem in developing countries.


    The application of international economics in current events is also 
emphasized in this course.


 

管理經濟學  


經四  選修  
(2 - 2)  


本科目主要在探討如何將個體經濟理論應用在消費者行為分析和企業經營決策上，結合經濟理論及統計計量的分析，探討如何有效解決企業面對的問題，幫助學生熟悉經濟概念並靈活的運用在不同產業結構下廠商的決策分析。


 


MANAGERIAL ECONOMICS

Senior elective  (2 - 2)

Managerial Economics brings together topics in microeconomics that 
can be applied to business decision making in various market structures. The 
objective of Managerial Economics is to help students understand and predict the 
economic forces shaping real-world business decisions and develop overall 
analytical skills of student.


 

勞動經濟學  


經四  選修  
(2 -2)  


本課程著重理論與實務的討論，先回顧勞動市場的現象，再試圖以理論來解釋。包含的主題有勞動供給、勞動需求、勞動均衡、補償薪資差異、人力資本投資、勞動力遷徙、勞動市場歧視與工作動機。

LABOR ECONOMICS

Senior elective (2 - 2)

This course reviews stylized 
facts in labor markets and tries to use theories to explain these facts. Topics 
discussed include labor supply, labor demand, labor market equilibrium, wage 
differential, human capital and investment, labor mobility, labor market 
discrimination, and work incentives.

 


